title: Cormac McGinley
text: Cormac McGinley is a former <a href="Gaelic%20football">Gaelic football</a>er who played for the <a href="Errigal%20Ciar%C3%A1n%20GAC">Errigal Ciarán</a> club and the <a href="Tyrone%20county%20football%20team">Tyrone county team</a>. He was a member of Tyrone's 2003 <a href="All-Ireland%20Senior%20Football%20Championship">All-Ireland</a> and <a href="National%20Football%20League%20%28Ireland%29">league</a> winning panel, although he took no part in the final. McGinley played his club football alongside Tyrone's <a href="Peter%20Canavan">Peter Canavan</a>, winning two <a href="Tyrone%20Senior%20Football%20Championship">Tyrone Senior Football Championship</a>s and the <a href="Ulster%20Senior%20Football%20Championship">Ulster Senior Football Championship</a>.
